cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.DS

The paper is primarily focused on logic programming and its implementation in the Oz language. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.PL (Programming Languages). However, the paper also discusses the wider context of multiparadigm programming, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.SE (Software Engineering) or cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also mentions the use of logic programming for algorithmic and search problems, which could place it in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
